CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 7, 1970, pg. 11 reads: "Number One - A happy Schenley High School basketball team gives the number one victory sign Tuesday afternoon after defeating Fifth Avenue and nailing down the championship in Section 1 of the City League. The Spartans now go against Carrick in the City Championship game on Friday afternoon at the Civic Arena.  On far left is Schenley Assistant Coach Bobby Young.  Head Coach Spencer Watkins is on right, standing in front of 67 Clarence Hopson.  Kneeling on the front row, on the left, is Ricky Coleman, who was the games top scorer with 26 points...Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of basketball championship winners Schenley High School including Assistant coach Robert Young on left, Leon Williams standing second from left, #22 Leonard Lesene, #67 Clarence Hopson wearing towel around neck, #51 Maurice Lucas, #32 Kenny Arnold, Ricky Coleman, Eddie "Fisher" Woods, and Head Coach Spencer Watkins on right
